{
  "stem": "13457.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I think a day or two later, the Germans came in.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And within two or three months, my aunt, Franka, that received us when we fled from Warsaw, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] her husband and her younger son that has the same name as I have, were all murdered by the death squads.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[CRYING] Anyway, so we're on our way.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "One stop was in Zhytomyr, then the next stop was in Kiev.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "By the time we got to Kiev, Kiev was already empty.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "In other words, there was nobody on the streets, and from what I realized late-- later, the Germans had already-- they had their pincer movement around Kiev, [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] and that's where they trapped out all these Soviet armies.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Anyway, we got out.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We were then on the train, again, living on the train, and we ended up not far from Stalingrad on one of the tributaries of Volga.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "We stayed there through the summer.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "The life was very quiet there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "It was a little village.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "But every day-- every day, anybody that wanted to hear the news realized that the Germans are cutting Stalingrad off from the north.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "That is to say that the-- that the link-- the railroad link, link with the-- inside Russia will be cut off.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we packed up these families, as I said, whatever number it was, five, six, or seven.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we went to Stalingrad.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was a mob of people.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There were thousands and thousands of people standing on the pier waiting for a ship [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] on Volga to go south to Astrakhan because there were still trains leaving Astrakhan.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Presumably, the day before the pier collapsed because it couldn't take the weight of all the people.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But anyway, the, the ship came.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
